http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/%E2%80%98Fight-against-destructive-forces%E2%80%99/article14022596.ece

Housing Minister M.H. Ambareesh has urged society to fight against destructive forces. Mr. Ambareesh, who is also the district in-charge Minister, spoke after hoisting the national flag, to mark the country’s 67th Republic Day at Sir M. Vivesvaraya District Stadium here on Tuesday. He also inspected the guard of honour by the police and other personnel.He said that India was globally known and respected for promoting peace and harmony.“Unfortunately, some destructive forces have been trying to create a sense of fear among people. Everyone should fight against such forces to protect the sovereignty and integrity of the country,” he said. Both the Union and State governments have been implementing various welfare schemes, he said and assured of taking steps to develop Mandya district.Students of various institutions performed various cultural activities.Deputy Commissioner M.N. Ajay Nagabhushan, Superintendent of Police C.H. Sudheer Kumar Reddy, Chief Executive Officer of the zilla panchayat B. Sharath and others were present.